#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "Stop Ecocide. Major Citizens’ Assembly in France"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "**18 JUN | France**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:59
msgid ""
"Buried in Coronavirus news over the past few months, **hugely exciting "
"things** have been [happening in "
"France.](https://www.franceinter.fr/environnement/les-150-propositions-de-la-convention-citoyenne-sur-le-climat)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:61
msgid ""
"The world's first major citizens' climate assembly has been hard at work "
"since October 2019. On 18 June they presented their **proposals for "
"addressing the climate emergency.**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:63
msgid ""
"The Convention Citoyenne pour le Climat (CCC) is an independent committee of "
"150 French citizens drawn by lot to reflect French diversity, with a mandate "
"to reduce French greenhouse gas emissions by at least 40% by 2030 while "
"advancing social justice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:65
msgid ""
"![French rebels and Youth For Climate activists show their support for the "
"CCC’s action plan.](/assets/uploads/10.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:67
msgid ""
"Convention members were divided into working groups to tackle a range of "
"social and economic issues and worked closely with climatologists and "
"economists, as well as economic and social organisations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:69
msgid ""
"The CCC has "
"[submitted](https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/06/21/la-convention-citoyenne-pour-le-climat-doit-rendre-ses-propositions-cet-apres-midi_6043625_3244.html) "
"149 proposals to Macron, "
"[including](https://propositions.conventioncitoyennepourleclimat.fr/): "
"measures addressing transport, energy, agriculture, and construction; "
"constitutional amendments to prioritise biodiversity; the creation of a new "
"body responsible for enforcing planetary limits; and a strong **call to make "
"ecocide a crime** by national referendum."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:71
msgid ""
"Organisers from the [Stop Ecocide](https://www.stopecocide.earth/) campaign "
"have [praised the "
"outcome](https://www.stopecocide.earth/press-releases-summary/french-citizens-assembly-votes-to-make-ecocide-a-crime-) "
"as phenomenal news."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Brussels Rebrands Finance to Resilience"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "**27 JUN | Brussels, Belgium**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:79
msgid "![Resilience Tower in Brussels.](/assets/uploads/12-min(1).png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:81
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Resilience Tower in "
"Brussels. "
"Photo:[@XR_Belgium](https://twitter.com/XR_Belgium?ref_src=twsrc%5Egoogle%7Ctwcamp%5Eserp%7Ctwgr%5Eauthor)*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**60 brave Belgian rebels were arrested** in Brussels while carrying out a "
"symbolic baptism of the city’s Finance Tower.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:85
msgid ""
"The tower had its name removed and was re-christened the Resilience "
"Tower. Each rebel carried a sign highlighting elements of our current "
"society that we need to leave behind and those we need to strengthen. Police "
"blocked rebels' attempts to continue their protest outside the Prime "
"Minister's office and arrested 60 of their number."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:87
msgid ""
"It was the culmination of [14 days of "
"actions](https://www.extinctionrebellion.be/en/june-action) across Belgium, "
"**stopping a ‘return to business as normal’** and calling for reflection on "
"the needs of society."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:89
msgid ""
"One rebel said: “We need to pause and think about what our needs are for the "
"future. Do we want to return to a system based on fossil fuels, industrial "
"agriculture, human exploitation and structural racism? Or work towards a "
"resilient society that recognises the urgency of the crises that await us?”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "Cooking Up a Protest Down Under"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:95
#, no-wrap
msgid "**7 JUL | Goulburn, Australia**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:97
msgid ""
"![Rebels staging the action outside the constituency "
"office](/assets/uploads/21.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:99
msgid ""
"Rebels staged[ a dramatic ‘Now we’re Cooking the Planet with Gas’ "
"action](https://www.facebook.com/xrnsw/videos/883650308795319/) outside the "
"constituency office of the Energy Minister in Goulburn, New South Wales."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:101
msgid ""
"They were protesting the government-appointed National Covid-19 Coordination "
"Commission’s **push for a ‘gas-led recovery’.** The NCCC is headed by and "
"stacked with gas industry executives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:103
msgid ""
"Natural gas consists mostly of methane, the second most significant "
"greenhouse gas after carbon dioxide and a key driver of the climate crisis."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hong Kong Demands Clean Air and Fair Rights"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "**28 JUN | Hong Kong**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:111
msgid "![Photograph of graveyard action.](/assets/uploads/11.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:113
msgid ""
"XR Hong Kong [staged a graveyard "
"action](https://hongkongfp.com/2020/06/29/in-pictures-extinction-rebellion-stage-graveyard-die-in-to-raise-awareness-of-hong-kong-pollution-deaths/) "
"to protest the destruction caused by air pollution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:115
msgid ""
"35 pairs of shoes were laid out to symbolize the 35 people who lose their "
"life from toxic air every week in Hong Kong. The city’s air pollutants "
"[consistently exceed "
"guidelines](https://hongkongfp.com/2019/09/08/clean-air-network-hong-kong-air-pollution-ngo-urges-govt-prioritise-public-health/) "
"set by the World Health Organization."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:117
msgid ""
"Worldwide, outdoor [air pollution kills more "
"people](https://academic.oup.com/cardiovascres/article/doi/10.1093/cvr/cvaa025/5770885) "
"than tobacco smoking. As one rebel put it: “Pollution kills not only humans "
"but all forms of life. The inaction of leaders is unacceptable.”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:119
msgid ""
"Two days later, Beijing’s [controversial national security "
"law](https://www.npr.org/2020/07/01/885900989/5-takeaways-from-chinas-hong-kong-national-security-law) "
"came into force. Thus curtailing the right to protest and risking the safety "
"of activists in Hong Kong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**“XR Hong Kong unwaveringly supports the fight of the Hong Kong people,”** "
"[the group "
"said](https://www.facebook.com/extinctionrebellionhk/photos/a.383584525640098/568669410464941/). "
"“Protecting human rights is protecting human lives.”\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:123
msgid ""
"People worldwide have shown their support for the people of Hong Kong. In "
"the UK, rebels [blocked access to an arms "
"factory](https://hongkongfp.com/2020/07/14/in-pictures-uk-activists-block-access-to-tear-gas-factory-in-solidarity-with-hong-kong-and-us-protests/) "
"to oppose exports of UK-manufactured rubber bullets and tear gas used to "
"suppress demonstrations in Hong Kong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:126
#, no-wrap
msgid "There Are No Emergency Exits"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "**29 JUN | Ängelholm–Helsingborg Airport, Sweden**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:131
msgid ""
"![Photograph of action with rebels holding banner \"Save the world OR "
"aviation.\"](/assets/uploads/3.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "*‘Save the World or Aviation’. Photo: XR Sverige.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:135
msgid ""
"A SAS domestic flight was delayed for an hour at Ängelholm–Helsingborg "
"Airport, when a brave [XRSweden](https://twitter.com/ExtinctionR_SV) rebel "
"‘superhero’ "
"[glued](https://www.facebook.com/extinctionrebellionsverige/videos/988024691658664/) "
"**herself to the plane.**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:137
msgid ""
"On the day Swedish airports reopened, rebels protested government bailouts "
"of the aviation industry as part of its Covid-19 recovery."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:139
msgid ""
"The rebels called on Sweden to stop funding polluters and use public money "
"to invest in green jobs and design a sustainable economy. They said: “Our "
"action was not directed at airline workers or individual passengers. **This "
"is about the need to change the whole system.”**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:141
msgid ""
"The non-violent protest was part of Extinction Rebellion Europe’s Bail Out "
"The Planet action wave. 5 rebels were briefly detained by the police."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:143
msgid "![Photograph of victorious Swedish rebels.](/assets/uploads/19.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Photo: XR Sverige.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:147
msgid ""
"In a second action on 29 June rebels delayed a SAS flight from Gothenburg to "
"Stockholm by [refusing to sit "
"down.](https://www.facebook.com/extinctionrebellionsverige/videos/3010068952552974/)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:149
msgid ""
"Rebels stated ‘These subsidies mean that Sweden cannot live up to the Paris "
"Agreement and its own climate goals (...) Just as I would break a car window "
"on a hot day to save a child or a dog, I sound an alarm because we are in a "
"planetary emergency.’"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:151
msgid "The rebels now face fines and **up to 6 months in jail.**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-07-16-newsletter-41.md:157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Once again we have too many actions for one newsletter. To catch up on all "
"the actions that have been happening around the world - and especially "
"during Europe's week-long wave of actions - you’ll have to [read XR "
"Unchained.](https://rebellion.global/blog/2020/07/16/xr-unchained-16/) It’s "
"choc full of beauty, courage, and inspiration.*\n"
msgstr ""

